article.description: — A'lahn Sumler scored 24 points and Charleston Southern beat Radford 58-57 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Sumler scores 24 as Charleston Southern beats Radford 58-57
article.linkText: Sumler scores 24 as Charleston Southern beats Radford 58-57
article.story: NORTH CHARLESTON, S.C. -- — A'lahn Sumler scored 24 points and Charleston Southern beat Radford 58-57 on Wednesday night. Sumler's jumper capped the scoring with 59 seconds left. Radford's Kenyon Giles missed a jumper with 39 second to play and DaQuan Smith missed a 3 to end it. Sumler shot 10 for 20, including 4 for 11 from beyond the arc for the Buccaneers (10-18, 6-9 Big South Conference). Taje' Kelly scored 13 points and added 10 rebounds. Daren Patrick had 10 points. Giles finished with 18 points to lead the Highlanders (15-15, 5-10). Smith added 15 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
